cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS 

This paper proposes a method to prune convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for deployment on embedded devices, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The method involves analyzing the importance of each channel via sparse reconstruction, which is a technique used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates the algorithm on CIFAR-100, which is a dataset commonly used in data science (cs.DS).
